# 9. Security in Hosted Runners

GitHub Hosted Runners are isolated environments.

---

# Security Features

| Feature               | Purpose         |
| --------------------- | --------------- |
| Fresh VM per job      | Isolation       |
| Automatic cleanup     | Removes data    |
| Temporary credentials | Better security |
| Sandboxed execution   | Reduced risks   |

---

# Important Security Note

Avoid printing:

* Secrets
* Tokens
* Passwords

Example bad practice:

```yaml
run: echo ${{ secrets.API_KEY }}
```

