# Final Understanding

GitHub Hosted Runners are cloud-based virtual machines provided by GitHub to execute workflows automatically.

They help create:

* Fast CI/CD pipelines
* Cross-platform testing
* Scalable automation
* Secure workflow execution
* Enterprise DevOps systems

Using GitHub Hosted Runners, developers can focus on:

* Writing code
* Building workflows
* Automating deployments

without managing infrastructure manually.
